Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createTrack(25.10)                                          createTrack(25.10)

Name
       createTrack  - Creates non-uniformed, customized tracks in selected de-
       sign area

Syntax
       createTrack

       [-help]

       -dir <direction>-layer <layerNameList>< >-num <numOfTrack>

       -start <coordinate>

       -step <step>

       Creates non-uniformed, customized tracks in selected design area. Typi-
       cally, the routing grid is generated when the floorplan is initialized.
       The first track is located at an offset from the placement grid set  by
       the  OFFSET  value  for the layer in the LEF file. The track spacing is
       the PITCH value for the layer defined in LEF.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each createTrack parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man createTrack.

       -dir <direction>
              Specifies track direction as a string.

       -start <coordinate>
              Specifies  the starting coordinate to create the track. The unit
              for the coordinates is user unit (micron).

       -num <numOfTrack>
              Specifies the number of tracks to create for the grid. You  can-
              not specify 0 numtracks.

       -step <step>
              Specifies the spacing between the tracks.

       -layer <layerNameList>
              Specifies the routing layer used for the tracks. You can specify
              more than one layer.

